---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Gold Loan | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Gold Loan</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Gold Loan</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Get instant funds by pledging your gold jewellery. Enjoy the lowest interest rates, minimal documentation, and quick disbursal within minutes at your nearest branch.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-bolt"></i> Quick Disbursal
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-file-check"></i> Minimal Docs
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i> Low Interest 7%+
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>Gold Loan Overview</h2>
          <p>A Gold Loan is one of the fastest and most accessible ways to raise funds in India. By pledging your gold ornaments or jewellery at a bank or NBFC, you can avail a loan of up to 75% of the gold's market value, as per RBI guidelines. The gold remains safely stored in the lender's vault until the loan is fully repaid.</p>
          <p>Gold loans are popular due to their simple eligibility criteria, quick processing (often within 30 minutes), minimal paperwork, and competitive interest rates starting from just 7% per annum. They are ideal for meeting short-term financial needs such as medical emergencies, business working capital, agricultural expenses, education fees, or wedding costs.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">7%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Interest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹25L</span>
              <span class="info-label">Maximum Loan Amount</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">3 Yrs</span>
              <span class="info-label">Maximum Tenure</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Gold Loan Interest Rates 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Max Loan Amount</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>SBI</td>
                <td>7.50% onwards</td>
                <td>₹20 Lakh</td>
                <td>36 Months</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Muthoot Finance</td>
                <td>7.35% onwards</td>
                <td>₹25 Lakh</td>
                <td>24 Months</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Manappuram Finance</td>
                <td>7.40% onwards</td>
                <td>₹25 Lakh</td>
                <td>24 Months</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Bank</td>
                <td>7.65% onwards</td>
                <td>₹15 Lakh</td>
                <td>24 Months</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>7.75% onwards</td>
                <td>₹10 Lakh</td>
                <td>12 Months</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Advantages of Gold Loans</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Instant disbursal — loan amount credited within 30 minutes of gold appraisal</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> No income proof or CIBIL score requirement for basic gold loans</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Lowest interest rates among all loan categories, starting at 7% per annum</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Flexible repayment options: bullet payment, EMI, or interest-only payments</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Gold is securely stored in bank-grade vaults with full insurance coverage</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> No restriction on end-use — funds can be used for any personal or business purpose</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Easy renewal and top-up facility available with most lenders</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Apply for a Gold Loan</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Visit a Branch</h4>
              <p>Walk into the nearest bank or NBFC branch with your gold ornaments and a valid photo ID proof.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Gold Appraisal</h4>
              <p>The lender's appraiser evaluates the gold purity and weight to determine the eligible loan amount.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Sign Agreement</h4>
              <p>Review and sign the loan agreement after verifying the interest rate, tenure, and repayment terms.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Get Funds Instantly</h4>
              <p>Receive the loan amount via bank transfer or cash (up to ₹20,000) within 30 minutes of approval.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Identity proof: Aadhaar card, PAN card, voter ID, or passport</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Address proof: Aadhaar card, utility bill, or rental agreement</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Passport-size photographs (2 copies)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Gold jewellery or ornaments (minimum 18 karat purity for most lenders)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Signed loan application form provided by the lender</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3>Apply for Gold Loan</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Gold Weight (approx. grams)" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block">Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3>Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/personal-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Personal Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Page CTA -->
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Turn Your Gold Into Instant Cash</h3>
          <p>Get the best gold loan rates from top banks and NBFCs with instant disbursal.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Talk to Expert <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">FAQs</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Everything you need to know about Gold Loans</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What is the minimum and maximum gold purity accepted for a gold loan? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Most banks and NBFCs accept gold jewellery with a minimum purity of 18 karats (75% gold content). Gold coins issued by banks are also accepted, but the weight of coins must not exceed 50 grams per customer. Gold bars, bullion, and coins from non-bank sources are generally not accepted for gold loans.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Is my gold safe when I pledge it for a gold loan? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, your gold is completely safe. All pledged gold is stored in high-security bank-grade vaults with CCTV surveillance and is fully insured against theft, fire, and natural disasters. You will receive a detailed receipt listing the weight, purity, and description of each item pledged. Your gold is returned in the same condition upon full repayment of the loan.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What happens if I am unable to repay the gold loan on time? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">If you are unable to repay the gold loan within the stipulated tenure, the lender will first send reminders and may offer a renewal or extension option (usually with an additional fee). If the loan remains unpaid after multiple notices, the lender has the legal right to auction your pledged gold to recover the outstanding amount. It is advisable to contact your lender and negotiate a renewal if you face repayment difficulties.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I get a gold loan without a CIBIL score or credit history? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, that is one of the biggest advantages of a gold loan. Since it is a fully secured loan backed by physical gold, most lenders do not check your CIBIL score or require any credit history. Your eligibility is primarily determined by the weight and purity of the gold you pledge. This makes gold loans ideal for first-time borrowers, homemakers, farmers, and individuals with no formal income proof.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">How is the gold loan amount calculated? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">The loan amount is calculated based on the Loan-to-Value (LTV) ratio set by the RBI, which is currently capped at 75% of the gold's market value. The lender's appraiser first determines the net weight of gold (excluding stones and other metals) and its purity. The per-gram rate of gold at the current market price is then multiplied by the net gold weight, and 75% of that value is the maximum loan you can get.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
